        Negative Gearing and Selling an Investment Property: CGT Implications for Brisbane Investors
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        When you sell a negatively geared investment property, the CGT clock has been running the whole time. Understanding how negative gearing history interacts with your capital gain is essential before you go to market.
      </p>
